== References == {{Reflist}}

'''Mohamed Afrah Hassan''' commonly knows as '''Mohamed Afrah''' (17 January 1974 – 7 April 2019) was a Maldivian film actor and producer.
{{Infobox person | name = Mohamed Afrah Hassan | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1974|1|17|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Thimarafushi (Thaa Atoll)|Th. Thimarafushi]], [[Maldives]] | death_date = {{death date and age|2019|4|7|1974|1|17|df=yes}} | death_place = [[Male']], [[Maldives]] | occupation = Actor, producer | years_active = 2000–2009 | spouse = | children = | honours = | alma_mater = }}
==Career== Afrah's first release in 2001 was Ali Shameel's drama film ''[[Hithi Nimun]]'' starred alongside [[Mariyam Nisha]], [[Mohamed Shavin]] and [[Sheereen Abdul Wahid]], which follows the storyline of a stubborn young man (played by Shavin) who abandons his girlfriend when he discovers about her pregnancy.<ref name=Top10Actresses>{{cite news|url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv:80/dhivehi/entertainment/117464 |title=Top 10 Actresses in Malives |language=Divehi|work=Haveeru |last=Nadheem |first=Ahmed |date=23 February 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120305014312/http://www.haveeru.com.mv:80/dhivehi/entertainment/117464 |deadurl=yes |archivedate=5 March 2012 |accessdate=26 November 2018}}</ref> In his second release of the year, Afrah was featured in Aslam Rasheed's romantic thriller film ''[[Dheevaanaa]]'' (2001) which was an unofficial remake of [[Ram Gopal Varma]]'s romantic thriller ''[[Pyaar Tune Kya Kiya]]'' (2001) starring [[Urmila Matondkar]], [[Fardeen Khan]] and [[Sonali Kulkarni]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rediff.com/movies/2001/apr/27pyaar.htm |title=Fatally Attracted |work=[[Rediff.com]] |date=21 April 2011 |author=Taparia, Nidhi |accessdate=16 November 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The film narrates the story of a woman who falls in love with an already married photographer and sets out to get what she wants, no matter what the consequences may be.<ref name=Top10Actresses/>
==Death== On 7 April 2019, Afrah was found dead lying on his bed at around 11:00 (Maldivian time) after he failed to wake up for breakfast.<ref name=death/> He was pronounced dead on taking to [[Indira Gandhi Memorial Hospital]].<ref name=death/> His [[Salat al-Janazah|funeral prayer]] was performed at Aasahara Moqsue after [[Isha prayer]].<ref name=death>{{cite news |url=https://www.muniavas.com/4049 |title=Actor, producer Afrah pronounced dead |language=Divehi|work=Muniavas |last=Rasheed |first=Ahmed |date=7 April 2018 |archiveurl=http://archive.is/AwdMA |deadurl=no |archivedate=8 April 2019 |accessdate=8 April 2019}}</ref>
